Interface IPubSubSyncChannelUpdate<T extends Serializable>

Type Parameters:
T - The type of data that is published.
All Superinterfaces:
IPubSubSyncChannelWatchOnly
public interface IPubSubSyncChannelUpdate<T extends Serializable> extends IPubSubSyncChannelWatchOnly
Represents a subscribed channel where the user can update the published data and thus sync all subscribers to the channel.
Author:
Stephen Wong (c) 2020

  • Method Details

    • update

      void update(IPubSubSyncUpdater<T> updateFn)
      Update the published data using the given updater function. Note that any new data elements would be encapsulated inside of the updater function. This will cause all subscribers to be synced with the new data.
      Parameters:
      updateFn - The updater function to use to update the published data.

    • unsubscribe

      void unsubscribe()
      Unsubscribe from the channel. This will disable both sync operations from the pub-sub server and update capability. The channel will be destroyed if this was the last subscriber.
      Specified by:
      unsubscribe in interface IPubSubSyncChannelWatchOnly
